<topic id="relax-ng-validation">
  <title>Validating Relax NG Schema Documents</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Relax NG schemas<indexterm>Validation</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>By default, Relax NG schema files are validated as you type. To change this, <ph
        conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/open-the-preferences-page"/>, go to <menucascade>
        <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Document Checking</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>, and deselect the <xref
        href="preferences-editor-document-checking.dita#preferences-editor-document-checking/enable-auto-validation"
          ><uicontrol>Enable automatic validation</uicontrol> option</xref>. </p>
    <p>To validate a Relax NG schema document manually, select the <uicontrol><image
          href="../img/Validate16.png" id="image_w5p_bsv_sr"/> Validate</uicontrol> action from the
          <uicontrol><image href="../img/ValidateDrop.png" id="image_sfz_bsv_sr"/>
        Validation</uicontrol> toolbar drop-down menu or the <menucascade product="developer editor">
        <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol>
      </menucascade><uicontrol product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">XML</uicontrol> menu. When
        <ph keyref="product"/> validates a Relax NG schema file, it expands all the included modules
      so the entire schema hierarchy is validated. The validation problems are highlighted directly
      in the editor, making it easy to locate and fix any issues.</p>
  </body>
